ETP Scores $319M Verdict In Pipeline Deal Breach Case



        By Jess Krochtengel



					Law360, Dallas (March 4, 2014,  4:05 PM EST) -- A Dallas jury on Tuesday found Enterprise Products Partners LP liable for more than $319 million in damages for its breach of a partnership agreement with Energy Transfer Partners LP to build a crude oil pipeline when it teamed up with a rival instead to build a similar line.In a unanimous verdict, the jury found co-defendant Enbridge USA Inc., Enterprise's partner on a crude oil line from Cushing, Okla., to refineries near the Gulf of Mexico, was not part of a conspiracy to exclude ETP...
				
