ETP Streamlines Claims In Advance Of $3B Pipeline Trial



        By Jess Krochtengel



					Law360, Dallas (September 13, 2013,  3:20 PM EDT) -- Energy Transfer Partners LP on Thursday streamlined claims from its $3 billion suit against Enterprise Products Partners LP and Enbridge USA Inc. over a scuttled oil pipeline joint venture, as the companies prepare for a three-week trial in Texas state court set to launch next week.ETP has accused Enterprise of breaching a 2011 joint venture agreement by replacing it with Enbridge as a partner in a 500-mile crude oil pipeline project running from Cushing, Okla. to Houston, cheating it out of what was then estimated...
				
