Azure Midstream Holdings





  Status: Active
  Headquarters: Houston, TX
www.azuremidstream.com

   In November 2013, Azure Midstream Holdings ("Azure") acquired TGGT Holdings ("TGGT") from Exco Resources and BG Group.  Simultaneously, Azure acquired East Texas Gathering ("ETG") from Tenaska Capital Management.  TGGT and ETG are natural gas gathering, transportation, treating and compression assets in East Texas and North Louisiana. The assets gather natural gas produced primarily from the Haynesville, Cotton Valley and James Lime formations.
  



Realized
Costar Midstream





  Status: Realized
  Headquarters: Dallas, TX

  Costar Midstream ("Costar") was formed in April 2011 to acquire and develop natural gas gathering and processing facilities principally in Texas and Oklahoma.  Costar acquired and developed multiple gathering and processing assets across Texas and North Dakota. These assets included the Gas Solutions system of over 500 miles of natural gas gathering pipelines, three cryogenic gas processing plants and associated compression and treating assets located in a four county area near Longview, Texas.  Costar also developed a natural gas gathering and processing system in West Texas primarily in Martin County and a Bakken crude oil gathering system in McKenzie County, North Dakota. In October 2014, the Company was sold to American Midstream Partners.
  



Active
Frontier Midstream Solutions





  Status: Active
  Headquarters: Tulsa, OK
www.frontierenergyllc.com

  In May 2014, Frontier Midstream Solutions ("Frontier") entered into a joint venture with Concho Resources Inc. (NYSE: CXO) to develop a crude oil transportation system in southeast New Mexico.  Phase 1 of the project will include 400+ miles of pipelines and 320,000 barrels of storage.  Frontier is pursuing additional crude oil projects in the Permian Basin that are complimentary to the joint venture with Concho.
  



Active
Kanata Energy Group





  Status: Active
  Headquarters: Calgary, Alberta Canada
www.kanataenergy.com

  Kanata Energy Group was formed in December 2012 to pursue midstream asset development and acquisition opportunities in Canada.
  



Active
Lakewood Midstream





  Status: Active
  Headquarters: Tulsa, OK
  Website: www.lakewoodmidstream.com

  Lakewood Midstream ("Lakewood") was formed in August 2013 to acquire and develop producer services assets in Texas and Oklahoma.  In August 2013, Lakewood acquired Itero Energy, a crude oil reclamation business serving the Permian Basin and Mid-Continent.  In November 2013, Lakewood acquired BS&W Solutions, a crude oil reclamation and water disposal business with assets that are complementary to Itero Energy's assets.
  



Active
 Liberty Midstream





  Status: Active
  Headquarters: Dallas, TX
www.libertymidstream.com

  Headquartered in Dallas, Liberty Midstream was formed in June 2013 to provide efficient, cost-effective gathering, treating, processing, compression and transportation services to oil and gas producers. Liberty’s three principals have a strong track record of over 65 years of experience in natural gas gathering, transportation and processing. The team has constructed and developed midstream assets in excess of $1 billion in the Barnett Shale, Marcellus, Midcontinent, East Texas, Louisiana and Permian.
  



Active
Prism Midstream





  Status: Active
  Headquarters: Bedford, TX
www.prism-midstream.com

  Prism Midstream ("Prism") was formed in September 2012 to provide infrastructure solutions for emerging resource plays.  Prism’s current assets include a rail terminal in West Texas near Pecos, Texas that provides transloading services, over 150 miles of gathering and transportation pipelines in Central Texas in Leon County, as well as a 50% non-operated interest in two natural gas pipeline systems along the Texas Gulf Coast.  Prism offers a full range of midstream services including crude and natural gas gathering, processing, treating, transloading, and salt water disposal.
  



