www.stonehengeenergy.com

  Stonehenge II was formed in June 2012 to pursue oil and gas gathering, processing and storage opportunities in the Ohio Utica Shale and Rocky Mountain regions.
  



Active
Tristate Midstream II





  Status: Active
  Headquarters: Denton, TX
www.tsmidstream.com

  Established in August 2011, Tristate Midstream II is focused on the acquisition and construction of natural gas gathering systems and processing facilities in Texas, Louisiana and Arkansas. In November 2012, the Company purchased substantially all of Forest Oil's natural gas gathering assets in East Texas.  The Company continues to expand this East Texas midstream footprint with additional acquisitions and new pipeline construction to serve producer customers.
  



Active
Velocity Midstream Partners





  Status: Active
  Headquarters: Tulsa, OK
www.velocitymidstream.com

  Established in January 2012, Velocity Midstream is focused on acquiring and constructing natural gas and liquids gathering, transportation, processing and storage systems in the United States. Velocity is currently building an oil gathering and transportation system in the SCOOP oil play in southern Oklahoma.  The anchor producer on the system is Continental Resources Inc. (NYSE: CLR), a large independent oil producer and the dominant leaseholder in the SCOOP with 470,000+ net acres.
  





