Realized
Aspen Pipeline I





  Status: Realized
  Headquarters: Houston, TX

  Aspen Pipeline I was formed in June 2006 with an initial investment in a small gas gathering system in Erath County, Texas. Since that time, Aspen's primary focus has been on the construction of a 50 MW biomass power plant in Lufkin, TX. The plant began operations in August 2011.
  



Realized
C&J Energy Services





  Status: Realized
  Headquarters: Houston, TX
www.cjenergy.com

  In October 2006, ESC invested in C&J, a coiled tubing and pressure pumping company primarily focused on the South Texas market. Since ESC's investment, C&J has expanded its operations significantly by opening new facilities in East Texas and Oklahoma, and by adding multiple fracturing and coil tubing fleets. These new assets have positioned the Company well to serve producers in the Haynesville and Eagle Ford Shale plays. C&J is continuing to expand its business through the addition of new fracturing and coil tubing equipment. In July 2011, C&J went public on the New York Stock Exchange (Ticker: CJES). In November 2012, ESC exited its remaining ownership in C&J.
  



Realized
Ceritas Energy I





  Status: Realized
  Headquarters: Houston, TX
www.ceritasgroup.com

  Ceritas I was formed in January 2005 with a strategy to acquire and grow natural gas gathering and processing assets. Ceritas I's first acquisition in March 2005 was a gas gathering and processing system in Liberty County, TX. The company was successful in attracting new gas to the system, as well as expanding the system and adding a 50 MMcfd processing plant. Ceritas I sold its Liberty System to DCP Midstream in June 2010 and its Optigas assets to Monarch Natural Gas Holdings in June 2012.
  



Realized
Clear Creek Energy Services





  Status: Realized
  Headquarters: Tulsa, OK

  Clear Creek Energy Services was a midstream energy company formed in June 2005 with a focus on the Powder River Basin in northeastern Wyoming and the Piceance Basin in western Colorado.
  



